The paper proposes a novel deep learning model for embedding hyper-networks, which is a topic related to network analysis and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also introduces a non-linear similarity function and uses deep learning techniques, which are common in the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves graph theory and optimization, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on different types of hyper-networks, which is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
